    Double the XDP fill ring depth

    ripatel-fd merged to firedancer-io/firedancer at 2025-02-19 00:50:53

    Double the XDP fill ring depth Fixes slight latency increases (~200ns) with some XDP configs. The XDP skb path seems to only consume fill ring entries when receiving a packet. The fill ring is thus mostly full for these configs. Consider a scenario where ksoftirqd consumes a packet, consumes a fill ring descriptor, and allocates a RX ring descriptor. When the net tile concurrently runs on a different CPU, it might have seen the updated cache line carrying the RX producer seqno, but not yet the FILL consumer seqno (data race). In this case, the net tile will refuse to consume the RX frag as it doesn't have space to return that frag to FILL (since FILL appeared full to it). The net tile then starts spinning (about 30 iterations or so on EPYC 7502P). By doubling the FILL ring depth, the net tile will always have enough space to return frags to FILL by the time the FILL cons seqno is updated.
